 Romania’s Simona Halep leaves the court after losing to Taiwan’s Hsieh Su-Wei in their women’s singles third round match on the sixth day of the 2018 Wimbledon Championships at The All England Lawn Tennis Club in Wimbledon, southwest London, on July 7, 2018. / AFP PHOTO / Oli SCARFF / RESTRICTED TO EDITORIAL USE  Hsieh, the world number 48, battled back from 2-5 down in the final set and halted Halep who served for the match at 5-3 in the decider. It will be Hsieh’s first appearance in the last 16 of a Slam where she will face Dominika Cibulkova of Slovakia for a place in the quarter-finals. “It’s my first win against a world number one,” said 26-year-old Hsieh. “It’s amazing. I was 2-5 down in the final set but the crowd pushed me to fight.”  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .